        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 12:57PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 1256 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Wayland to near Allegan. Movement was
southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Kalamazoo...           Hastings...            Allegan...
Wayland...             Otsego...              Plainwell...
Middleville...         Parchment...           Richland...
Martin...              Westwood...            Comstock Northwest...
Gull Lake...           Dorr...                Alamo...
Orangeville...         Irving...              Hopkins...
Moline...              Delton...
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
